        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer39351210" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer801325574072643982">A friend of mine (a pure mathematician) says that the Glass Bead Game is obviously pure mathematics in a thinly disguised form. It&apos;s not exactly a slam-dunk, but I&apos;m still surprised how few people there are who seem to believe this theory. You&apos;d think it would at least be a respectable minority opinion.<br/><br/>Turn it around: if the Game isn&apos;t pure mathematics, what is it? Just something he made up, that doesn&apos;t refer to any real intellectual discipline in particular, but is a hypothetical synthesis of </span>
  <span id="freeText801325574072643982" style="display:none">A friend of mine (a pure mathematician) says that the Glass Bead Game is obviously pure mathematics in a thinly disguised form. It's not exactly a slam-dunk, but I'm still surprised how few people there are who seem to believe this theory. You'd think it would at least be a respectable minority opinion.<br /><br />Turn it around: if the Game isn't pure mathematics, what is it? Just something he made up, that doesn't refer to any real intellectual discipline in particular, but is a hypothetical synthesis of all of them? Are there any other reasonable alternatives? Personally, I rather like the "pure mathematics" account.<br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="801325574072643982" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

