  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3498269290" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3498269290" />
    <a title="Oleksandr Zholud" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4743119-oleksandr-zholud"><img alt="Oleksandr Zholud" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1506182069p2/4743119.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3498269290?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Oleksandr Zholud" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Oleksandr Zholud" href="/user/show/4743119-oleksandr-zholud">Oleksandr Zholud</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9660315163" href="/book/show/22811972">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3498269290" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6051097976934104473">This is the last novel by <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1113469.Hermann_Hesse' title='Hermann Hesse' rel='nofollow noopener'>Hermann Hesse</a>, it won Retro-Hugo for the best novel of 1943 in 2019. While it is not a ‘true’ SF, more a classic utopia, set in (as the author suggested) in the 23rd century. I read is as a part of monthly reading for August 2020 at <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/group/show/474371-hugo-nebula-awards-best-novels' rel='nofollow noopener'>Hugo &amp; Nebula Awards: Best Novels</a> group. I used 1978 Ukrainian translation of the text.<br/><br/>This is a classic bildungsroman i.e. a literary genre that focuses on the psychological and moral growth of the protagonist from youth to adulthood (comin</span>
  <span id="freeText6051097976934104473" style="display:none">This is the last novel by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1113469.Hermann_Hesse" title="Hermann Hesse" rel="nofollow noopener">Hermann Hesse</a>, it won Retro-Hugo for the best novel of 1943 in 2019. While it is not a ‘true’ SF, more a classic utopia, set in (as the author suggested) in the 23rd century. I read is as a part of monthly reading for August 2020 at <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/group/show/474371-hugo-nebula-awards-best-novels" rel="nofollow noopener">Hugo &amp; Nebula Awards: Best Novels</a> group. I used 1978 Ukrainian translation of the text.<br /><br />This is a classic bildungsroman i.e. a literary genre that focuses on the psychological and moral growth of the protagonist from youth to adulthood (coming of age), in which character change is important. In this case it is a story of Joseph Knecht (from German ‘servant’), who for his talents is taken to the pedagogical province of Castilia (from Ancient Greek: Κασταλία, in Greek mythology, was a naiad-nymph, a daughter of Achelous who inhabited the Castalian spring in Delphi that could inspire the genius of poetry to those who drank her waters or listened to their quiet sound). One of the main things that Castilians do is play the Glass Bead Game.<br /><br />The Glass Bead Game is based on the idea that everything is linked to everything, like a music melody can be represented with math, which in turn can be linked to astronomy. Players start with one item and show how it is linked to everything else. From one hand, the players know and study a great deal, on the other they assume that nothing new can be created, so they fawn about old, but add nothing new. <br /><br />The novel is written as a “wall of text” with paragraphs sometimes several pages long. I’d greatly prefer it cut at least twofold, maybe even more. Added to the novel there are writings of Knecht himself (three novellas and poetry), which are very good, better than the novel itself. The poetry was translated by famous Ukrainian poetess <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/19571571._____________" title="Ліна Костенко" rel="nofollow noopener">Ліна Костенко</a>.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6051097976934104473" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

